The above and other objects, features and advantages of the present invention will become more apparent from the following detailed description made with reference to the accompanying drawings. In the drawings:


FIG. 1 is a schematic diagram showing an air conditioner system for electric vehicles according to a embodiment of the present invention;


FIGS. 2A and 2B are tables showing, respectively, relations among electromagnetic valves and a four-way switching valve in each operation mode of the embodiment, and relations among compressor operations, sensor outputs and exterior fan operations in each operation mode of the embodiment;


FIG. 3 is a front view showing a air conditioner control panel in the embodiment;


FIGS. 4A, 4B and 4C are graphs showing, respectively, a relation between a temperature feeling and a set temperature in the embodiment, a relation between an exterior air temperature and an exterior air temperature deviation in the embodiment, and a relation between a solar radiation and a solar radiation deviation in the embodiment;


FIG. 5 is a flow diagram showing an entire operation of an air conditioner control unit in the embodiment;


FIG. 6 is a flow diagram showing a defrosting operation of the air conditioner control unit in the embodiment;


FIG. 7 is a graph showing a relation between an exterior air temperature and a defrosting time period in a modified embodiment; and


FIG. 8 is a graph showing a relation between a high pressure and a compressor rotation speed in another modified embodiment.
